OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776301390
OL,3,CBadenoch: Only Tories will stand up
OL,4,Cagainst SNP's 'divisive' referendum
OL,5,Cplans
OL,7,FSNP leader and Scottish First Minister
OL,8,FJohn Swinney has vowed to push for a
OL,9,Fsecond independence referendum if his
OL,10,Fparty wins an overall majority of
OL,11,Fseats in the Scottish Parliament.
OL,13,FMrs Badenoch is expected to say the
OL,14,FSNP remains "completely obsessed with
OL,15,Ftearing our country apart".
OL,17,FShe will add: "John Swinney has been
OL,18,Fvery clear he will use a majority in
OL,19,Fthe Scottish Parliament to press ahead
OL,20,Fwith another divisive referendum."
OL,26,@vD@MOUwD@ZO]yD@OOU|D@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
